You are hungry! Let's cook a delicious meal. Check the cookbook in the kitchen for the recipe. Once done, enjoy your meal!

-= Kitchen =-
You've moved into a typical room. Your mind races to think of what kind of room would be typical. And then it hits you. Of course. You're in the kitchen. You can barely contain your excitement.

Oh wow! Is that what I think it is? It is! It's a fridge. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see an oven. Suddenly, you bump your head on the ceiling, but it's not such a bad bump that it's going to prevent you from looking at objects and even things. You can make out a table. You see a cookbook on the table. You see a counter. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a counter? On the counter you see a red hot pepper and a knife. You make out a stove. The stove is conventional. But the thing is empty.

There is a closed plain door leading east. There is an exit to the north. There is an exit to the south.
